EnviroStar, Inc. Key Developments

EnviroStar, Inc. Announces Unaudited Consolidated Earnings Results for the Third Quarter and Nine Months Ended March 31, 2017
May 15 17
EnviroStar, Inc. announced unaudited consolidated earnings results for the third quarter and nine months ended March 31, 2017. For the nine months, the company reported revenues were $67,523,000 compared to $27,623,000 for the same period a year ago. Operating income was $4,340,000 compared to $2,100,000 for the same period a year ago. Income before income taxes was $4,228,000 compared to $2,102,000 for the same period a year ago. Net income was $2,570,000 compared to $1,310,000 for the same period a year ago. Net income allocated to company’ shareholders was $2,463,000 compared to $1,310,000 for the same period a year ago. Basic and diluted earnings per share were $0.27 compared to $0.19 for the same period a year ago.

For the quarter, the company reported revenues were $24,653,000 compared to $12,760,000 for the same period a year ago. Operating income was $1,499,000 compared to $1,241,000 for the same period a year ago. Income before income taxes was $1,437,000 compared to $1,242,000 for the same period a year ago. Net income was $890,000 compared to $774,000 for the same period a year ago. Net income allocated to company’ shareholders was $853,000 compared to $774,000 for the same period a year ago. Basic and diluted earnings per share were $0.08 compared to $0.11 for the same period a year ago.


EnviroStar, Inc. Announces Unaudited Consolidated Earnings Results for the Six and Three-Month Periods Ended December 31, 2016
Feb 13 17
EnviroStar, Inc. announced unaudited consolidated earnings results for the six and three-month periods ended December 31, 2016. For the six months ended December 31, 2016, revenues increased by 188% to approximately $42.9 million from approximately $14.9 million for the same period of fiscal 2016. For the first six months of fiscal 2017, EVI generated operating income and net income of approximately $2.8 million and $1.7 million, respectively, or $0.19 per share, compared to operating income and net income of approximately $860,000 and $536,000, respectively, or $0.08 per share, for the same period of fiscal 2016. Income before income taxes was $2,791,000 against $861,000 a year ago. 

For the second quarter ended December 31, 2016, revenues increased by 287% to approximately $33.4 million from approximately $8.6 million in the comparable period of fiscal 2016. Operating income and net income for the second quarter of fiscal 2017 was approximately $2.3 million and $1.3 million, respectively, amounting to net earnings of $0.13 per share, compared to operating income and net income of approximately $607,000 and $379,000, respectively, amounting to net earnings of $0.05 per share, for the second quarter of fiscal 2016. Income before income taxes was $2,226,000 against $608,000 a year ago.


EnviroStar, Inc. Appoints Robert Lazar as Chief Accounting Officer and Vice President of Finance
Jan 4 17
On January 3, 2017, Robert Lazar was appointed Chief Accounting Officer and Vice President of Finance of EnviroStar, Inc. Mr. Lazar, age 52, previously served as Chief Accounting Officer and Vice President of Finance for Steiner Leisure Limited, where he was employed since 2000. Prior to joining Steiner Leisure Limited, Mr. Lazar worked in various capacities at Arthur Andersen LLP, including as Senior Manager from 1995 to 2000.


